values:
Its time again for me to update this journal, or perhaps I should say....
Dear Christian, (since of course he is the only one who reads it which is fine)
I am sitting at work still thinking about how crazy life can be.  I will never cease to be amazed at the every day happening that come about just by sitting back and observing. Not that I do that alot because I am so high strung I usually like to be in on most of the action. I do however have to say...that, though trite and rather repetitive I think it is time for me to turn over a new leaf. Ahh, yes, shocked I can tell.  It is hard to live in a reality that you wish was true only to be shown day by day that what you want, or wish you had, is just quite honestly not there. I speak vaguely because as 7 Mary 3 says "If I stay lucky then my tounge will stay tied and I won't betray the things that I hide"  I guess I can be majorly overly analytical especially when i am completely aware of the situation. But since  you are lost I will just say that Christian, I am glad you are back to your regular schedule. I missed you. And when I say that you make my day happier and make my life better I mean it. God Bless you Sebastian!
always

I have a really issue with people who think you owe them the world.  You know what I got is a big ole BITE ME...for those people.  
Anywhoooo....ITS CASUAL FRIDAY....WAAAAAAAAAAAH HAA! Good news we are also having casual Monday. I really need a life, because the fact that i get to wear jeans excites me.  
Today is a sleepy day.  If i could i would crawl under my desk and take a nap. But i am sure that probably wouldn't go over very well with Big Brother.

abby

Well here i sit at work...counting the minutes until i can close out my day and hit the road to the house! I am sleepy!  

I hope that all 3 of my live journal friends had a good day! ha! ha!

its 8:52 ... i only have 8 minutes left...

I hear batches calling my name

TUPAC & Biggie :)
~abby

Tomorrow I have to work.
But hey, somone has to pay the bills :)
Ya'll have a great night!
See C & C tomorrow!

Here is my question...why is there not some sort of test to let people spend money
I mean not everyone should be able to sign themselves up for utilities such as water, gas, electricity, or CABLE.
Some people are too stupid!
Oh Lord forgive me for I am mean, but god help us all!
HAHA

Lets discuss spatial profiling for a moment
The funniest statement of the day perhaps.

Its the middle of January
Why still the Christmas Music?

If i could hybernate like a bear. I would.
Today is a sleepy day.
Plus my cell is screwed.

Its been a long time since I have written.  Written for the sake of opening my heart and letting thoughts poor out, emotions, feelings.  I used to write all the time.  In a phase where i was head strong but weak at heart.   Now I look back over those times and i think i see myself as a different person.  Still astounded by life but yet I now have a more yielded, cautious and cynical view.  Me a cynic? Few would think so, and in all actuality I hope people see me as an optimistic one who sees the glass as half full...as trite as that may be.  I guess the one thing you discover with growing up is that there is no one out there who is normal.  No one grew up with a white picket fence and a bike with a basket while being totally to the core of their soul, happy.  Life is just not satisfying to most and for good reason.  I can't remember a time in my life when I look back and have felt totally satisfied.  Why would you want to feel that way? You would have nothing else to aspire to, nothing else to want, nothing else to be.  My friends have always made a joke of the fact that someday I should write a book.  The life and times of a girl with a outrageous personality.  Someone who enjoyed emotion to the polar opposite ends of the spectrum.  I was always one who faked happiness in order to prove to the people that she loved that I wasn't a failure. I have always been a pleaser. One who sought approval but in contradiction one who never compromised.  Comprimised as far as human ethic... I have never allowed for a tolerance of people who do not respect human life and  the fact that a person is more than a name and a face but a being, a masterpiece of complex thought, emotion, and desires.  Anyway, I think the book might be a good one.  Love, pain, illness...has the makings of a Danielle Steele story.  HA HA! Not quite as boosom-y or breath taking. now that i have blabbed about tons of absolutely nothing. i am going to get back to work....ahhhhh go hea!

Okay So here is the thing...I am quite illeterate in the online world.  I mean I can check my email and find everything from a watch to a antique Queen Anne chair on ebay, but as for this online journal business I can actually say I am a virgin.
So today is a new day. Exciting!
